        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 68–71. Cybaeus ubicki spec. nov., males from California, left palpus (68–69, 71 from Novato, 70 from Anchor Bay). 68–69 Patella and tibia (68 retrolateral, 69 dorsal). 70–71 Genital bulb (70 ventral, 71 retrolateral). E—embolus, PA—proximal arm of tegular apophysis. RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis. Unlabelled arrows indicate dorsal tibial ridge and dorsal prominence of patellar apophysis." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4752607/files/figure.png" .

